			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p954">Input mapper</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=954&amp;sid=cd74e8ddb7621f2fec220ea53a9143e7#p954"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=103&amp;sid=cd74e8ddb7621f2fec220ea53a9143e7">Arthegal</a></strong> &raquo; 18 Jun 2011, 06:24 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Hi,<br />What do you think about implementing an input mapper inside the engine?<br />Take far example the CameraFirstPerson, keys and mouse are assigned inside the camera, this cause problems for example for exucution of code on differents computers with different keyboard layout W(up) S(down) D(right) A(left) that should be on another computer ZSQD (azerty keyboard). Another problem is what if i would prefer using a gamepad, my remote control or my kinect to control theses actions.....<br />Having a FPSCamera with abstract actions controls (Up Down, .....) (that could be defined has analog (0....1) or digital(0/1)), and having a possibility to map inputs to theses controls could be great....<br />Imagine if you set camera Up has a analog action control, if we map digital W key to Up action, it is full or no speed, if we map a gamepad analog stick to the up action, it will be varying speed.....and mapping digital input to analog action would be possible too.<br />This will also introduce the possibility to control the camera from new input peripherals without having to modify the FpsCamera class.<br /><br />Hope that someone has understood the idea, cause i'm bad for exlpainations..... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />Have a nice day <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_wink.gif" alt=";-)" title="Wink" /></div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile954">
