	<div id="p956" class="post bg2">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p956">Re: Input mapper</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=956&amp;sid=cd74e8ddb7621f2fec220ea53a9143e7#p956"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54&amp;sid=cd74e8ddb7621f2fec220ea53a9143e7" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">tpastor</a></strong> &raquo; 18 Jun 2011, 12:06 </p>

			

			<div class="content">i totally agree with you !!! =P<br />The FirstPersonCamera is just an example of camera implementation, it is used only for the demos. Like a facility for us.<br />In a production environment, you should implement the ICamera abstract class and define your own camera with the right input management.<br />In the engine we have an input facility (IntroductionDemos Input sample) that make the life a little easier, but we dont have an abstraction like you are describing.<br />In Engine development, there is always a dilema about how for the engine should go: Some features should not belong to the engine, some should. It is very hard to make the distinction (if we implement too much, the engine becomes heavyweight and too specific, if we dont implement enough it becomes useless).<br /><br />I really liked yout suggestion and i will put it in our to do list.<br />=P</div>

			<div id="sig956" class="signature">PloobsEngine<br />Creator and Developer<br />ploobs.com.br/?page_id=1381</div>

		</div>

		
